<refnamediv><refname>imtexture</refname><refpurpose>Compute local texture statistic maps.</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>result = imtexture(image)
result = imtexture(image, window)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>Input image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>window</term><listitem><para>Scalar or two-element local window size. Default is <literal>[7 7]</literal>.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>result</term><listitem><para>Structure containing local <literal>Mean</literal>, <literal>Std</literal>, <literal>Entropy</literal>, and <literal>Contrast</literal> maps.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection>
<refsection><title>Description</title><para>Returns a structure containing Mean, Std, Entropy, and Contrast maps from a sliding neighborhood.</para></refsection>
<refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/opencv_fruits.jpg"));
image = imresize(rgb2gray(image), [120 160]);
result = imtexture(image, [7 7]);
subplot(1, 2, 1);
imshow(image);
subplot(1, 2, 2);
imshow(result.Contrast, hot(64));]]></programlisting></refsection>
